<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                        <head>No. 145.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Pierrepont</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-11-24"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 24,
                                    1876</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Pierrepont</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister, London:</hi></p>
                        <p>Interview this day with Thornton makes it possible that British
                            Government may surrender Winslow, Brent, and Gray without conditions. If
                            offer be made of all or of either, you will accept, and are authorized
                            to appoint trustworthy person to convey fugitive without delay to United
                            States.</p>
                        <p>Inform me immediately by telegraph in cipher whatever be done in the
                            premises.</p>
                        <closer><signed>FISH, <hi rend="italic">Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>